Class EmergencyService

java.lang.Object
EmergencyService
public class EmergencyService
extends java.lang.Object
Class whose instances represent a hospital's Emergency Service Unit.
Author:
Miguel Nunes fc56338

    • checkIn

      int checkIn​(UrgencyStatus urgency, int consultationTime)
      Registers the entrance of a new patient, with given urgency and consultation time, to this Emergency Service Unit.
      Parameters:
      urgency - Patient's urgency code.
      consultationTime - Time required to treat the Patient.
      Returns:
      The patient's identification number.
      ?Requires:?
      consultationTime >= 0

    • chooseDoctor

      int chooseDoctor()
      Determines the doctor to assign the next patient to according to the following criterion:
      - The smallest waiting time;
      - Least number of patients;
      - Least number of urgent patients;
      - Smallest doctor identification number.
      Returns:
      The chosen doctor's identification number.

    • assignPatient

      Parameters:

      patientId - Patient's identification number.
      ?Requires:?

      Patient has not been assigned to any doctor yet.

    • idSearch

      private int idSearch​(int patientId)
      Searches for the index position of the given identification number in the List of checked-in patients using searchRecursion(). This method exists solely to make calling searchRecursion() more convenient.
      Parameters:
      patientId - Identification number to search for.
      Returns:
      Index position of the given identification number.
      ?Requires:?
      totalPatients() > 0

    • searchRecursion

      private int searchRecursion​(int patientId, int lowerBound, int upperBound)
      Recursive binary search method used by idSearch to search for the index position of the given identification number in the List of checked-in patients.
      Parameters:
      patientId - Identification number to search for.
      lowerBound - Lower index bound, inclusive.
      upperBound - Upper index bound, inclusive.
      Returns:
      Index position of the given identification number.
      ?Requires:?
      lowerBound >= 0 && upperBound < totalPatients() && lowerBound <= upperBound
